name: Indy Caps
description:
The Indianapolis Capitols were the Circle City's first pro football team. Playing in their home games at Bush Stadium as part of the Continental Football League they won the CFL Championship in 1969. Relive history with this T printed on soft American Apparel Jersey Cotton. The discharged image will wear with every wash giving it a vintage look and feel.

name: No Mean City
description:
"I am a citizen of no mean city" paraphrases Acts 21:39. What Paul meant was to say that the city he is from is important and anything but average or ordinary. On the cornerstone of the Old Indianapolis City Hall these words are inscribed, "I am, myself, a citizen of no mean city." These words were placed there by Mayor Charles Bookwalter so no one would pass by “without feeling the responsibility for good citizenship in this city of ours.” Shirt: American Apparel TriBlend Indigo Design: Water based ink and foil
